				[c/8f8f8f:"Encompassing Universe,Interlacing Qiankun"]
				'''
		}

		Revelation: {
			DisplayName: Revelation
			Tooltip:
				'''
				Hold down left-click to grip the Revelation, releasing it after one second if you hold up the left-click.
				Releasing earlier than one second reduces damage; the shorter the time, the greater the penalty.
				Right-click to manually destroy an existing Revelation.
				Hitting enemies five times increases the weapon’s level, starting at level 0.
				Level 0—Small explosion on hit.
				Level 1—Small increase to damage, speed, and explosion range.
				Level 2—Significant glow, major damage increase, and tracking light bolts accompany its flight.
				Level 3—Further damage increase, explosion form change, and elemental mix in explosions.
				Level 4—Further speed increase, explosions release numerous tracking comets.
				Taking damage or missing enemies will decrease one level.
				Unequipping the weapon clears its ALL level; re-equipping it does NOT restore levels.
				[c/494949:"Condensed with all of humanity's technology, incomprehensible to outsiders."]
				'''
		}

		SoulSeekerJav: {
			DisplayName: Apex Remnant
			Tooltip:
				'''
				Upon hitting an enemy, begins spiraling and continuously releases fireballs.
				Each hit summons one Supreme Soul Seeker, which orbits the player.
				These orbiters deal contact damage and perform coordinated strikes alongside the lance.
				Right-click to command all orbiters to dash at enemies, applying a one-second Vulnerability Hex.
				Up to 10 Supreme Soul Seekers can exist; at full count, the lance deals increased damage on hit.
				Obtained by performing necromantic infusion on the Gilded Proboscis, reversible via Shimmer.
				[c/630000:"The dragon is a Whispering spiral, drawing fundamental power from the world's fractured soul, growing relentlessly until the finale."]
				'''
		}

		PrimordialState: {
			DisplayName: Yin-Yang Genesis
			Tooltip:
				'''
				Begins homing after flying for a short while.  
				During this phase, generates a Yin-Yang Orb every 12 frames.  
				Each orb continuously follows the lance and deals rapid damage.  
				After homing ends, the lance darts off in a random direction,  
				emitting additional orbs on departure.  
				Orbs bounce on impact and detonate in dual-aspect explosions.  
				[c/e1ffff:"Thus comes judgment—there is no gray."]  
				[c/2f2f2f:"Yet truth lies hidden between the black and white."]  
				'''
		}

		StarsofDestiny: {
			DisplayName: Chronoseeker
			Tooltip:
				'''
				Left-click hurls the Clock Lance's long hand, forming a temporal array.
				Right-click releases the short hand, a seeker that hunts targets on its own.
				Each left-click strike inscribes a Time Mark, and every mark empowers your next right-click attack.
